==English==
[[Category:Russian names]]
===Etymology===
A [[Romanization]] of the Russian surname [[Ржевский]].

===Proper noun===
'''Rzhevsky'''

#Lieutenant '''Rzhevsky''' is a fictional young cavalry officer who appears in numerous popular Russian jokes that poke fun at social sophistication and decorum while interacting with various characters from the novel '''''[[War and Peace]]''''' by Leo [[Tolstoy]].

